1.Customer searches for available cars on the rental company's website or mobile app that we will create for both platforms.
2.Customer selects a car and enters their rental dates.
3.Customer fills out personal and payment information.
4.Rental company confirms availability and reserves the car for the customer
5.Customer receives a rental agreement and rental instructions via email or text message.
6.Customer picks up the car at the designated location and presents a valid driver's license and credit card.
7.Customer drops off the car at the designated location at the end of the rental period.
8.Rental company inspects the car for any damage or excess mileage.
9.Rental company charges the customer's credit card for the total cost of the rental, including any additional charges such as fuel or tolls.
10.Customer has the right to leave the review and comments he got.
